Document: GPUParticlesCollisionSDF3D
Path: godot/classes/class_gpuparticlescollisionsdf3d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the GPUParticlesCollisionSDF3D node, which controls particle collisions using a 3D signed distance field.

Property Descriptions
bake_mask (int): The visual layers to account for when baking the particle collision SDF. Only MeshInstance3D nodes whose VisualInstance3D.layers match with this bake_mask will be included in the generated particle collision SDF. By default, all objects are taken into account for the particle collision SDF baking. Default: 4294967295.
Method: set_bake_mask(value: int)
Method: get_bake_mask() -> int

resolution (Resolution): The bake resolution to use for the signed distance field texture. The texture must be baked again for changes to the resolution property to be effective. Higher resolutions have a greater performance cost and take more time to bake. Higher resolutions also result in larger baked textures, leading to increased VRAM and storage space requirements. To improve performance and reduce bake times, use the lowest resolution possible for the object you're representing the collision of. Default: 2.
Method: set_resolution(value: Resolution)
Method: get_resolution() -> Resolution

size (Vector3): The collision SDF's size in 3D units. To improve SDF quality, the size should be set as small as possible while covering the parts of the scene you need. Default: Vector3(2, 2, 2).
Method: set_size(value: Vector3)
Method: get_size() -> Vector3

texture (Texture3D): The 3D texture representing the signed distance field.
Method: set_texture(value: Texture3D)
Method: get_texture() -> Texture3D

thickness (float): The collision shape's thickness. Unlike other particle colliders, GPUParticlesCollisionSDF3D is actually hollow on the inside. thickness can be increased to prevent particles from tunneling through the collision shape at high speeds, or when the GPUParticlesCollisionSDF3D is moved. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_thickness(value: float)
Method: get_thickness() -> float
